Package: gov.noaa.messageapi.conditions

[Java] Class ComparisonCondition

      • gov.noaa.messageapi.conditions.ComparisonCondition
      • All Implemented Interfaces and Traits:
        IComparisonCondition

        public class ComparisonCondition
extends BaseCondition

        A comparison condition is a condition type that holds basic/fundamental comparisons - things like <,>,=,/=, etc. Comparison condition extends the BaseCondition.

        Authors:
        Ryan Berkheimer

        • Constructor Detail

          • public ComparisonCondition(java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Object> conditionMap)

            Constructor for creating a new ComparisonCondition from a map. This is usually used by the schema when bootstrapping a new session.

            Parameters:
            conditionMap - A map holding all required condition parameters.

          • public ComparisonCondition(IComparisonCondition condition)

            Copy constructor for creating a new ComparisonCondition from an existing one. This is generally used in immutable operations when creating new records during request building.

            Parameters:
            condition - The original condition to copy

        • Method Detail

          • public java.lang.String getField()

            The field (as a name string) referenced by the comparison condition. All comparison conditions correspond to one field.

            Returns:
            The field name corresponding the the field to which the condition applies

          • public java.lang.Object getValue()

            Returns the value held by the condition. Values are generalized objects. The value is cast during comparison operation against field values.

            Returns:
            The value held by a condition as an object.

          • public void setValue(java.lang.Object value)

            Sets the condition value for the condition. Any object type is a valid value.

            Parameters:
            value - The value to associate with the condition
